    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc_tb.00779.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <note type="authorial" place="top">Send a <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/></note>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place">Melt<supplied reason="illegible" resp="#smb" cert="medium">onsville Alabama</supplied></name>
                    <date when="1875"><gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/><unclear reason="illegible" resp="#smb" cert="low">13</unclear> 1875.</date>
                </dateline>
                <salute>Walt Whitman <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> <supplied reason="illegible" resp="#smb" cert="medium">Dear</supplied>friend</salute>
            </opener>

            <p><gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/>t of this letter, I wish you to know that tho'
                    raised in what might fairly be called a
                backwoods country, and with no means naturally at hand to learn the <hi
                    rend="underline">etiquette</hi> of "society", I yet fully understand the nature
                of my acquaintance with you&#8212;it is a sort of "literary" acquaintance
                <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> I would not feel free <gap reason="illegible"
                    extent="unk"/> into <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> reco<gap
                    reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> friend <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/>
                <hi rend="underline">takes</hi>
                <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> sheet of <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"
                /> no r<gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/>
                <hi rend="underline">throughout</hi> the
                <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/>, I don't <unclear reason="illegible" resp="#smb" cert="low">present</unclear>
                to <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> gentlemanly to present one's self with
                some boldness in that way. The strongest of my motives all along has been to <hi
                    rend="underline">give you pleasure and be paying back</hi> for what I have
                received. Yet I have also thought of <hi rend="underline">a good moral effect on my
                    family</hi> from their seeing their <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/>," win<gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/>ognition
                from <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/>e in my <gap reason="illegible"
                    extent="unk"/>k of <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> yet <unclear
                    reason="illegible" cert="medium" resp="#me">about</unclear>
                <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> might <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/>a<gap reason="illegible" quantity="1" unit="char"/>
                <hi rend="underline">insane</hi> or a <hi rend="underline">drunk</hi> man. <hi
                    rend="underline">And I then</hi> doubted whether you could admit the possibility
                of such conditions producing such <hi rend="underline">sanely</hi> insane
                writing.</p>
            <p>(P.S. I know <hi rend="underline">you must think</hi> there has been a "level-headed"
                    <hi rend="underline">theory</hi> to my life.)</p>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="loc_tb.00781.jpg" type="verso"/>
            <p>Now <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> occasionally that <unclear
                    reason="illegible" cert="medium" resp="#km">you</unclear>
                <hi rend="underline">still</hi> live&#8212;for the <hi rend="underline"
                    >Scripture</hi> says "the dead know not anything, nor is there any more a reward
                for them &amp;c &amp;c.<ptr target="loc.01848_n4"/> A mere Postal card can tell me that. But if you get tired of
                writing that sort of letters only, I will tell you what more to write of. First tell
                me of some of <hi rend="underline">the things that make you happy</hi>, or at least
                    <hi rend="underline"><unclear reason="illegible" cert="high" resp="#me"
                        >alleviate</unclear></hi> your distressed condition. <choice>
                    <sic>Dont</sic>
                    <corr>Don't</corr>
                </choice> you <unclear reason="illegible" resp="#smb" cert="high">wish to</unclear>
                tell <unclear reason="illegible" resp="#smb" cert="low">some</unclear>thing about the Centennial <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/>
                expect <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> of the <gap reason="illegible"
                    extent="unk"/> John Burroughs<ptr target="n0129"/>
                <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> is it <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/>
               thi<gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> <hi rend="underline">seem to be</hi>
                <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/>. Are all the good things of life dead with
                you are you now only <hi rend="underline">enduring</hi> life? Please forgive me if I
                be now impertinent&#8212;I have not been so in <hi rend="underline">asking
                    questions</hi> before, and I <hi rend="underline"><choice>
                        <sic>cant</sic>
                        <corr>can't</corr>
                    </choice> compel</hi> you to answer.</p>
            <p>Your card of July 2<ptr target="n5002c"/> acknowledged my letter of June 27, but
                didn't mention my letters of June 10 or 12<ptr target="n5002h"/>&#8212;I like to
                know <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> get <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"
                /> from me, in <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> ground <gap reason="illegible"
                    extent="unk"/> of what <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> correspondence
                    <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> not to <unclear reason="illegible"
                    cert="medium" resp="#km">write</unclear>
                <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> questions <gap reason="illegible"
                    extent="unk"/> with <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/>, because while my <hi
                    rend="underline">original and unprompted ideas</hi> would necessarily in most
                cases be <hi rend="underline">only a repetition</hi>
                <pb xml:id="leaf002r" facs="loc_tb.00782.jpg" type="recto"/> of what others
                <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/>ght <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/>
                <hi rend="underline">long</hi> ago, on th<gap reason="illegible" extent="two words"
                />and <hi rend="underline"><gap reason="illegible" extent="two words"/></hi>
                <gap reason="illegible" extent="one word"/> <unclear reason="illegible" resp="#smb" cert="low">past</unclear> 
                civilization and mastering it".
                Therefore I must not be in a hurry to commence on such things and be giving you my
                "meagre" thoughts.</p> 

            <p>I think what will please you best, will be for me to write about myself, my
                circumstances, my <hi rend="underline">practical</hi> philosophy, my mother, father,<ptr target="loc.01839_n4"/>
                and <unclear reason="illegible" cert="medium" resp="#km">others</unclear>
                <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> Yet I <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/>
                not be<gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/>
                <hi rend="underline">ma</hi><gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> But as <unclear reason="illegible" resp="#smb" cert="low">for</unclear> <gap
                    reason="illegible" extent="unk"/>
                <hi rend="underline">eccent</hi><gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/>
                <hi rend="underline">so free</hi>
                <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> <unclear reason="illegible" resp="#smb" cert="low">tricity</unclear> with me. My eccentricity lies in my adherence
                to <hi rend="underline">all Nature</hi> and <hi rend="underline">my own nature</hi>
                and following the straight path of <hi rend="underline">good practical common
                    sense</hi> in such a way as most people are not capable of. You and I, <hi
                    rend="underline">you and I</hi> "fly the flight of the fluid and swallowing
                    soul,<ptr target="loc.01848_n1"/> and our <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/>
                before <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> of <gap reason="illegible"
                    extent="unk"/>
                <unclear reason="illegible" cert="low" resp="#nhg">underst</unclear><gap
                    reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> illustr<gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/>k
                wiser for <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> fool folks <gap reason="illegible"
                    extent="unk"/> one in this way&#8212;while I am not at all <gap
                    reason="illegible" extent="one word"/> or <hi rend="underline">contentious, and
                    seldom have an enemy</hi>, there is yet in my nature (which I can't help) so
                much of the principle of <hi rend="underline">destructiveness</hi> or <hi
                    rend="underline">mortal revenge</hi> that I am constantly <pb xml:id="leaf002v"
                        facs="loc_tb.00783.jpg" type="verso"/> fe<gap reason="illegible"
                    extent="unk"/> put upon me the fatal <gap reason="illegible" extent="one word"/>
                and very <unclear reason="illegible" cert="high" resp="#km">injurious</unclear>
                provocation. Also (so much the worse for me) I have always had a leaning towards <hi
                    rend="underline">suicide</hi> as a relief in case of great trouble&#8212;Walt!
                can you require absolutely of me as a condition of friendship that I shall change
                the deepest grounded elements of my <hi rend="underline">nature</hi>? "Can the
                leopard change his spots, or the Ethiopian his skin?"<ptr target="loc.01848_n3"/></p>
            <p>I think <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> something <gap reason="illegible"
                    extent="unk"/>ery much content you with a <unclear reason="illegible"
                    cert="medium" resp="#me">sketch</unclear>
                <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> natural philosopher, <gap reason="illegible"
                    extent="unk"/> was mar<gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> together 3 yrs.
                    <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/>bined in th<gap reason="illegible"
                    extent="unk"/> all) would be quite a <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"
                />&#8212;but <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> I was only 8&#8212;to be his son
                has been a sort of patent of nobility here if I can judge rightly of
                appearances.&#8212;</p>
            <p>I have got along mighty well with my crop, and hindered the boys from school very
                little so far&#8212;they stand at the head of their classes&#8212;<hi
                    rend="underline">by divine right.</hi></p>
            <p>Little Walt at the age of 7 months &amp; 20 days commenced very suddenly to crawl
                over the floor in "bully" style <gap reason="illegible" extent="one word"/> 3 days
                    ago&#8212;<gap reason="illegible" extent="one word"/> Nov 18 <unclear
                    reason="illegible" cert="high" resp="#km">1874</unclear>&#8212;<gap
                    reason="illegible" extent="unk"/>, and <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/>
                skinned) child <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> and <gap reason="illegible"
                    extent="unk"/> to improve my <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> this summer
                after "laying by" the crop. What pleases me most is that you and I seem to be agreed
                that what America and the world need is to have not saints or angels but merely <hi
                    rend="underline">good enough</hi> people and allowing some difference in
                directions of action.</p>
            <closer>
                <signed>J.N.J.</signed>
            </closer> 
